solution: ```class Solution {
    public int[] pivotArray(int[] nums, int pivot) {
        int n = nums.length;
        int[] res = new int[n];
        int less = 0, greater = 0;
        for (int num : nums) {
            if (num < pivot) less++;
            else if (num > pivot) greater++;
        }
        int equal = n - less - greater;
        int i = 0, j = less + equal;
        for (int num : nums) {
            if (num < pivot) res[i++] = num;
            else if (num > pivot) res[j++] = num;
        }
        while (equal-- > 0) res[i++] = pivot;
        return res;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Single pass to count elements, second pass to place them in order; stable partitioning without extra data structures.

